This recipe will teach you how to prepare mouth-watering tahini date bars that are not only quick and easy to make but taste delicious as well. Ingredients: - 250ml nutty wheat flour - 5ml baking powder - 310ml desiccated coconut - 250g dates, pitted and roughly chopped - 7ml ground nutmeg - 5ml ground cinnamon - 3 eggs - 125ml brown sugar - 180ml tahini - 60ml sesame seeds READ: Stout caramel popcorn - recipe Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 160Â°C. 2. Grease and line a 17x26cm lamington pan. 3. Combine the flour, baking powder and 250ml desiccated coconut, dates and spices in a bowl. 4. Use an electric beater to beat the eggs and sugar until light and fluffy. 5. Gradually add the tahini and beat on low until just combined. 6. Pour the tahini mixture into the flour and stir with a metal spoon until just combined. 7. Pour into the prepared pan and smooth the surface with the back of a spoon. 8. Sprinkle with the remaining coconut and the sesame seeds. 9. Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until a skewer inserted comes out clean. 10. Remove from the oven and cool for 15 minutes. 11. Turn out onto a board and cut into squares. READ: Delicious pistachio & lemon madeira loaf cake - recipe Makes 15 squares